# Design Conventions

Design to the LocalIQ brand, not a generic SaaS look. Reference `files/ui-tokens.md` and reuse existing components before building new UI.

## Tokens and components

- Use CSS variables (`--color-*`, `--space-*`, `--radius-*`, `--font-*`) from `globals.css` / `ui-tokens.md`.
- Never hardcode hex colors, arbitrary spacing (`p-[13px]`), or one-off radii.
- Prefer existing shared components; extend them rather than duplicating patterns.

```tsx
// ❌ BAD
<div className="bg-[#534AB7] p-[18px] rounded-3xl" />

// ✅ GOOD
<div className="bg-[var(--color-brand)] p-[var(--space-5)] rounded-[var(--radius-md)]" />
```

## Typography and color

- At most two typefaces: `--font-sans` (Inter) and `--font-mono` (JetBrains Mono).
- One accent color: `--color-accent` (teal). Brand purple (`--color-brand`) is for primary actions, not decoration.
- Use the typography scale (`text-h1`, `text-body`, etc.) for hierarchy — size and weight, not extra colors or shadows.

## Layout and motion

- Brand-first hierarchy: clear headings, restrained whitespace, content over chrome.
- Restrained motion: short, purposeful transitions; no decorative animations.
- No hero cards, gradient banners, or oversized rounded corners. Max radius: `--radius-lg` (14px) unless a token says otherwise.

## Responsive

- Build mobile-first; scale up with breakpoints.
- Before finishing UI work, verify layout in preview at mobile and desktop widths.
